		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<h3 class="show-factsh3">
				Two unique facts about Switzerland
			</h3>
		</div>
			
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Located deep underground in Switzerland is a 17 mile-long tunnel and a mega machine called the Large Hadron Collider. It has been designed to conduct tests to recreate and reveal the conditions that existed immediately following the Big Bang, which created the universe 13.7 billion years ago. Beams of Protons (subatomic particles found in the nucleus of an atom) are sent around the tunnel at 99.9 % the speed of light before colliding with one another, creating temperatures 100,000 times hotter than the sun.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
